{"ts":"2026-06-27T15:00:41.547Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining Initial Setup**\n\nOkay, I've outlined the core replacements needed, specifically focusing on initial state. I'm importing `useEffect` and `useCallback` now too, for handling the data fetching logic effectively. I'm focusing on the hooks and the load function; I'm pretty pleased with my current approach!\n\n\n**Analyzing UI Implementation**\n\nI'm now focusing on implementing the UI updates. I've pinpointed the relevant section in `/app/portal/ai-operations/page.tsx`, specifically lines 555-665, and am analyzing how the `filteredAgents` data renders within the active telemetry list. I've re-reviewed lines 555 to 570 for context on the filtering display.\n\n\n**Implementing Loading States**\n\nI'm now focusing on the loading, error, and empty states. I'll integrate skeleton loaders during loading, and a custom error card if something goes wrong. For the empty list scenario (after loading or with no results), I will display a dedicated empty state component. I'm writing the empty state code for the UI right now.\n\n\n**Defining Error Components**\n\nI'm now writing the `OperationsErrorState` component to handle telemetry desync errors. The component will render a card with an error message and a retry button. I'm focusing on making the error UI visually clear and informative to help the user understand the problem and take action.\n\n\n**Designing UI Refresh**\n\nI'm now integrating the \"Re-establish Handshake\" button into the WorkspaceCard, creating a clear action for users. I'm focusing on the component's styling and functionality. I'm also now designing the corresponding loading state; I'm implementing a skeleton loader block within the `WorkspaceCard`, aiming for a visually appealing and informative loading experience.\n\n\n**Integrating Telemetry View**\n\nOkay, I'm now integrating this loading, error, and agent display logic within the `activeTab === \"telemetry\"` section of the page. I'm focusing on the component structure and data flow, and I am making sure the existing components integrate well. I'm taking another pass on the display of `WorkspaceCard` now, as well.\n\n\n**Refining No-Results State**\n\nNow I'm focusing on the \"no results\" state. I've got the `OperationsEmptyState` for initial empty states, and a no-results display for filtered scenarios. I'm carefully refining the UX, making sure the user is informed and has clear options, like resetting filters, if there are no agents after filtering!\n\n\n"}}
