{"ts":"2026-06-27T15:06:24.705Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"pmjcm477","input":{"summary":"Successfully connected the client portal AI Operations dashboard (/portal/ai-operations) and AI Operation detailed page (/portal/ai-operations/[id]) to the backend REST API endpoints (/api/v1/ai-operations and /api/v1/ai-operations/[id]).\n\nHere is a summary of the implementation and validation steps taken:\n\n1. Shared Mapping Helper: Created `mapping-helper.ts` inside `/app/portal/ai-operations` to dynamically transform backend `ApiAiOperation` records into high-fidelity `EnrichedAgent` frontend state objects with proper formatting, specific telemetry metrics (dynamic and stable cpu, ram, latency, uptime), and custom eBPF event stream logs.\n2. Connected AI Operations Dashboard (/portal/ai-operations):\n   - Refactored the dashboard to fetch operation records using React's useCallback/useEffect hooks.\n   - Incorporated authorization headers containing the user's secure token (`gff_ai_access_token` from local storage), automatically ensuring client users see only their client_id scoped records.\n   - Added highly refined visual states including `OperationsSkeleton` (shimmering loaders), `OperationsErrorState` with a robust and premium \"RE-ESTABLISH HANDSHAKE\" retry button, and `OperationsEmptyState` for an empty registry.\n   - Connected system runtime count dynamically to show `agents.length` REPL sandboxes.\n   - Kept all premium Phase 4 interactive filters (search, project, type, status, stage), tab systems (telemetry, hardware diagram, governance), and \"Recycle Core\" cold reboot simulators completely functional and dynamic.\n3. Connected AI Operation Detail Page (/portal/ai-operations/[id]):\n   - Hooked up `useParams` dynamic lookup to retrieve enclave parameters from `/api/v1/ai-operations/[id]`.\n   - Programmed premium skeletons, full network error card with retry option, and custom StatusBadge type-safeguards.\n   - Dynamically populated model attributes, AMD SEV-SNP/Intel SGX silicon maps, neural parameter mappings, and active eBPF event streams from the backend API.\n   - Maintained full operational capability for the premium simulated \"Verify Attestation\" physical HSM keys module.\n4. Validation & Quality Checks:\n   - Executed the backend API test script (`scripts/test-ai-operations-apis.js`) to verify CRUD/REST logic with 100% success.\n   - Performed static type audits via `npx tsc --noEmit` to guarantee full type safety and zero compiler warnings.\n   - Ran `npm run lint` and confirmed ESLint rules pass flawlessly without errors.\n   - Assured there are no changes made to the landing page or external GFF AI tools. All layout parameters correspond strictly with GFF AI's Constitution guidelines (premium, strategic, responsive, and calm colors).","verified":true}}}
